## 1 Introduction

Waves occur in many natural phenomena such as seismic waves in earthquakes and ocean waves. Due to their periodic behavior, these waves are commonly modeled by the two trigonometric functions, sine and cosine.

In one computer generated visual simulation, it showed that MV Derbyshire, the biggest British registered merchant ship ever to have been lost at sea, was sunk by typhoon Orchid because the ocean waves at the time of incident were just slightly longer than 294 metres, the length of the ship. This meant that her bow would have been submerged before she had the chance to rise above the waves.

