## 3 Inverse of Trigonometric Functions

\[y=\sin x \Leftrightarrow x=\sin^{-1}y.\] \[y=\cos x \Leftrightarrow x=\cos^{-1}y.\] \[y=\tan x \Leftrightarrow x =\tan^{-1}y.\]

Note that \(\sin^{-1}x\) denotes the **inverse** of \(\sin x\). It is **NOT** the reciprocal of \(\sin x\), i.e.

\[\sin^{-1}x\neq\dfrac{1}{\sin x}=\big{(}\sin x\big{)}^{-1},\qquad\big{(}\tan^ {-1}x\big{)}^{2}\neq\tan^{-2}x=\dfrac{1}{\tan^{2}x}.\]

