## 4 Trigonometric Identities

A trigonometric identity expressed in terms of \(x\) is an equality that involves trigonometric functions, and is true for all values of \(x\) (except possibly at singular points where the trigonometric function is not defined).

The basic trigonometric identities are as follows:

